        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 4:19PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 418 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Leasburg, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Leasburg, Las Cruces, Radium Springs, Dona Ana, Fairacres, Mesilla,
East Mesa, Picacho, Hill, Northeast Las Cruces, Corralitos, Las
Cruces West Mesa, Fort Selden State Historic Site, and Leasburg Dam
State Park.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 10 in New Mexico between mile markers 130 and 140.
Interstate 25 in New Mexico between mile markers 1 and 21.
Highway 70 in New Mexico between mile markers 150 and 155.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
